      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Wide open race despite the scratching of a leading chance and just a small field. LADY GALADRIEL (4) is a lightly raced mare with a great record this course and distance. Was safely held in the Vamos Stakes two back then not far away in a Class 4 latest. Well-suited here and gets a chance to return to winning form. GOLDEN MEADOW (3) hasn't been far away last two and both in open class. Don't underestimate back in grade. SKY LAND (7) has been kept fresh for this after racing in tougher grade over further. Another who can atone. STREET DIVA (6) ran on strongly for third last time and can sneak into the finish again.",
